Syria is \"prepared\" on the return of refugees, according to the Minister for Foreign Affairs
Syria declares itself ready for the voluntary return of refugees and calls for assistance in rebuilding this war-torn country for more than seven years.
Addressing the United Nations General Assembly, Foreign Minister Walid al-Moualem stated that the situation in the country was improving.
\"Today, the situation on the ground is more stable and safer thanks to the progress made in the fight against terrorism,\" he said.
The government continues to rehabilitate areas destroyed by terrorists in order to restore normalcy.
All conditions are now met for the voluntary repatriation of refugees to the country that they were forced to leave because of terrorism and unilateral economic measures aimed at their daily lives and livelihoods.
The United Nations believes that more than 5.5 million Syrians have deserted the country since the beginning of the war in 2011.
Six other million people still living in the country need humanitarian assistance.
Al-Maualem stated that the Syrian regime would welcome aid for the reconstruction of that devastated country.
He stressed, however, that he would not accept conditional assistance or assistance from countries sponsoring the insurrection.
